const formatCurrency = (val) => new Intl.NumberFormat('en-IN', { style: 'currency', currency: 'INR', maximumFractionDigits: 2 }).format(val);
const formatNumber = (val) => new Intl.NumberFormat('en-IN', { maximumFractionDigits: 2 }).format(val);
---
<SiteLayout site="westmount" title={meta.title} description={meta.description} canonical="https://westmountfundamentals.com/top-intraday-stocks-today-india" schema={JSON.stringify(schema)}>
  <div class="page-content container">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Top Intraday Stocks Today India</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Looking for high volume movers? Our daily analysis of liquidity and volatility helps you spot opportunities.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="methodology-section card">

    <section class="advanced-strategies">
      <h2>Advanced Strategies for Intraday Trading in Indian Markets</h2>
      <p>Mastering the art of intraday trading requires far more than merely selecting a high-momentum stock. To thrive, traders must understand complex market mechanics, leverage advanced tools, and implement rigorous risk management frameworks. This section delves into the granular tactics professional traders use to navigate the dynamic landscape of Indian equities.</p>

      <h3>1. Liquidity and Order Book Analysis</h3>
      <p>Intraday traders heavily rely on Level 2 market data to analyze the depth of the order book. By observing the volume of resting limit orders at various price levels, traders can identify significant supply and demand zones that are not immediately apparent on a standard price chart. In the context of the <a href="/top-intraday-stocks-today-india">top intraday stocks today in India</a>, high liquidity implies that large block orders can be executed with minimal slippage. Recognizing spoofing—where fake orders are placed to create a false sense of demand or supply—is a crucial skill. A sudden withdrawal of massive limit orders often precipitates sharp, unexpected price reversals.</p>

      <h3>2. Volume-Weighted Average Price (VWAP) Integration</h3>
      <p>The Volume-Weighted Average Price (VWAP) is the single most important indicator for intraday institutional traders. Unlike moving averages that only consider closing prices, VWAP incorporates both price and volume, providing a true measure of the day's average transaction price. Traders often use VWAP as a dynamic support or resistance level. A stock trading above its VWAP is generally considered to be in an intraday uptrend, while one trading below is in a downtrend. More importantly, mean-reversion strategies often target the VWAP as a reversion point during overextended price runs. If you are comparing strategies across different time horizons, such as those found in our guide on <a href="/top-long-term-investment-stocks-india-2025">top long term investment stocks india 2025</a>, you will notice that intraday metrics like VWAP rarely matter for multi-year holds.</p>

      <h3>3. Gap and Go vs. Gap Fill Scenarios</h3>
      <p>Indian markets frequently experience gap-ups or gap-downs at the open, driven by overnight global cues, SGX Nifty movements, or pre-market earnings announcements. A "Gap and Go" strategy involves buying a stock that gapped up and exhibits strong opening volume, betting on continued momentum. Conversely, a "Gap Fill" strategy assumes that the initial emotional reaction is overextended and the price will mean-revert back to the previous day's close. Identifying which scenario is playing out requires analyzing the pre-market volume and the conviction of the first 15-minute candle.</p>

      <h3>4. Sector Rotation and Thematic Plays</h3>
      <p>Intraday momentum rarely exists in a vacuum. It is often dictated by broader sector rotations. For example, if the Bank Nifty index is experiencing a heavy sell-off, attempting to go long on a mid-cap banking stock is fighting the current. Advanced traders monitor sector indices in real-time. If IT stocks are outperforming, capital is quickly rotated into high-beta IT constituents. This thematic approach is distinct from broader macroeconomic strategies used when selecting the <a href="/best-performing-stocks-july-2025">best performing stocks july 2025</a> in global markets.</p>

      <h3>5. Risk Management and the 1% Rule</h3>
      <p>The most sophisticated strategy is useless without draconian risk management. The golden rule of intraday trading is to never risk more than 1% to 2% of total trading capital on a single trade. This means calculating position sizes based on the distance between the entry price and the logical stop-loss level, rather than simply buying a fixed number of shares. Professional traders also utilize trailing stop-losses to protect unrealized gains during extended intraday runs, adjusting the stop level behind significant swing lows or moving average dynamic supports.</p>
    </section>


      <h2>Methodology: How We Rank</h2>
      <p>For day trading in India, our primary ranking metrics focus on <strong>liquidity</strong> and <strong>intraday volatility</strong>. We prioritize stocks with extremely high average daily trading volumes to ensure traders can execute large orders without significant slippage. We also factor in the stock's beta relative to the Nifty 50, sector momentum, and recent price action to determine the best candidates for capturing intraday swings.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="filter-section card">
      <h2>Filter Stocks</h2>


      <div class="filter-controls" style="margin-bottom: 1rem; display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <label for="sectorFilter">Sector:</label>
        <select id="sectorFilter" style="padding: 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); background: var(--bg-color); color: var(--text-primary);">
          <option value="all">All Sectors</option>
        </select>

        <label for="yieldFilter">Min Yield:</label>
        <select id="yieldFilter" style="padding: 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); background: var(--bg-color); color: var(--text-primary);">
          <option value="all">Any</option>
          <option value="1">1%+</option>
          <option value="3">3%+</option>
          <option value="5">5%+</option>
        </select>

        <label for="marketCapFilter">Min Market Cap:</label>
        <select id="marketCapFilter" style="padding: 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); background: var(--bg-color); color: var(--text-primary);">
          <option value="all">Any</option>
          <option value="10B">10B+</option>
          <option value="50B">50B+</option>
          <option value="100B">100B+</option>
        </select>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="table-section">
      <h2>Summary Comparison</h2>
      <div class="table-wrapper">
        <table id="stocksTable">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th data-sort="rank">Rank &#x21D5;</th>
              <th data-sort="name">Company &#x21D5;</th>
              <th data-sort="volume">Volume &#x21D5;</th>
              <th data-sort="price">Price (INR) &#x21D5;</th>
              <th data-sort="sector">Sector &#x21D5;</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {stocks.map(stock => (
              <tr data-sector={stock.sector}>
                <td>{stock.rank}</td>
                <td><strong>{stock.symbol}</strong><br/><small>{stock.name}</small></td>
                <td>{formatNumber(stock.volume)}</td>
                <td>{formatCurrency(stock.price)}</td>
                <td>{stock.sector}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="rankings-section">
      <h2>Detailed Stock Analysis</h2>
      {stocks.map(stock => (
        <article class="card stock-card" data-sector={stock.sector}>
          <div class="card-header">
            <div class="rank-badge">{stock.rank}</div>
            <h3>{stock.name} ({stock.symbol})</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="card-stats">
            <div><strong>Price:</strong> {formatCurrency(stock.price)}</div>
            <div><strong>Volume:</strong> {formatNumber(stock.volume)}</div>
            <div><strong>Sector:</strong> {stock.sector}</div>
            <div><strong>Beta:</strong> {stock.beta.toFixed(2)}</div>
          </div>
          <p><strong>Why it's ranked here:</strong> {stock.why}</p>
          <div class="pros-cons">
            <p><strong>Pros:</strong> {stock.pros}</p>
            <p><strong>Cons:</strong> {stock.cons}</p>
          </div>
        </article>
      ))}
    </section>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      {faqs.map(faq => (
        <details>
          <summary>{faq.question}</summary>
          <p>{faq.answer}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </section>
  </div>
  <script is:inline>
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {

    const sectorFilter = document.getElementById('sectorFilter');
    const yieldFilter = document.getElementById('yieldFilter');
    const marketCapFilter = document.getElementById('marketCapFilter');

    // Populate sectors dynamically based on table data
    const sectors = new Set();
    const rows = document.querySelectorAll('tbody tr');

    rows.forEach(row => {
      // Assuming Sector is the 2nd column (index 1)
      const sector = row.children[1] ? row.children[1].textContent.trim() : '';
      if (sector) sectors.add(sector);
    });

    sectors.forEach(sector => {
      const opt = document.createElement('option');
      opt.value = sector.toLowerCase();
      opt.textContent = sector;
      if (sectorFilter) sectorFilter.appendChild(opt);
    });

    const applyFilters = () => {
      const sectorVal = sectorFilter ? sectorFilter.value.toLowerCase() : 'all';
      const yieldValStr = yieldFilter ? yieldFilter.value : 'all';
      const mcValStr = marketCapFilter ? marketCapFilter.value : 'all';

      const minYield = yieldValStr === 'all' ? 0 : parseFloat(yieldValStr);
      let minMC = 0;
      if (mcValStr === '10B') minMC = 10; // in Billions
      if (mcValStr === '50B') minMC = 50;
      if (mcValStr === '100B') minMC = 100;

      rows.forEach(row => {
        const rowSector = row.children[1] ? row.children[1].textContent.trim().toLowerCase() : '';
        const rowYieldText = row.children[3] ? row.children[3].textContent.trim() : '0'; // Assuming Yield is 4th col
        const rowMCText = row.children[4] ? row.children[4].textContent.trim() : '0'; // Assuming MC is 5th col

        const rowYield = parseFloat(rowYieldText.replace(/[^0-9.]/g, '')) || 0;

        let rowMCInBillions = 0;
        let mcNum = parseFloat(rowMCText.replace(/[^0-9.]/g, '')) || 0;
        if (rowMCText.includes('T')) rowMCInBillions = mcNum * 1000;
        else if (rowMCText.includes('B')) rowMCInBillions = mcNum;
        else if (rowMCText.includes('M')) rowMCInBillions = mcNum / 1000;
        else rowMCInBillions = mcNum;

        const matchSector = sectorVal === 'all' || rowSector === sectorVal;
        const matchYield = rowYield >= minYield;
        const matchMC = minMC === 0 || rowMCInBillions >= minMC;

        if (matchSector && matchYield && matchMC) {
          row.style.display = '';
        } else {
          row.style.display = 'none';
        }
      });
    };

    if (sectorFilter) sectorFilter.addEventListener('change', applyFilters);
    if (yieldFilter) yieldFilter.addEventListener('change', applyFilters);
    if (marketCapFilter) marketCapFilter.addEventListener('change', applyFilters);


    // Sorting Logic
    const getCellValue = (tr, idx) => tr.children[idx].innerText || tr.children[idx].textContent;
    const comparer = (idx, asc) => (a, b) => ((v1, v2) =>
      v1 !== '' && v2 !== '' && !isNaN(v1.replace(/[^0-9.-]/g, '')) && !isNaN(v2.replace(/[^0-9.-]/g, '')) ?
      v1.replace(/[^0-9.-]/g, '') - v2.replace(/[^0-9.-]/g, '') :
      v1.toString().localeCompare(v2)
    )(getCellValue(asc ? a : b, idx), getCellValue(asc ? b : a, idx));

    document.querySelectorAll('th').forEach(th => th.addEventListener('click', (() => {
      const table = th.closest('table');
      const tbody = table.querySelector('tbody');
      Array.from(tbody.querySelectorAll('tr'))
        .sort(comparer(Array.from(th.parentNode.children).indexOf(th), this.asc = !this.asc))
        .forEach(tr => tbody.appendChild(tr));
    })));
  });
</script>
  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    .card-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .rank-badge { background: var(--accent-color); color: white; width: 2.5rem; height: 2.5rem; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.2rem; }
    .card-stats { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-bottom: 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .pros-cons { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--bg-color) 80%, var(--card-bg)); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; margin-top: 1rem; }
    .pros-cons p { margin: 0.5rem 0; }
    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    .table-wrapper { overflow-x: auto; }
    th { cursor: pointer; background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--bg-color) 80%, var(--card-bg)); font-weight: 600; }
    th, td { padding: 0.75rem 1rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    tr:hover { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--card-bg) 80%, var(--accent-color) 10%); }
    .faq-section details { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 1rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .faq-section summary { font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .filter-controls { margin-top: 1rem; }
    .filter-controls select { padding: 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); background: var(--bg-color); color: var(--text-primary); }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
